1. General Principles

Always follow the SDLC phases (requirements → design → implementation → testing → deployment → maintenance).

Prioritize security, scalability, and maintainability in every decision.

Use modular, clean, and documented code with strict version control (Git + branching strategy).

Ensure human-readable logs and error handling across frontend and backend.

Follow 12-factor app methodology for cloud-native design.

2. Backend Engineering Rules

Use Node.js (Express/Prisma) or Python (FastAPI/Django) depending on module needs.

Design APIs as REST + GraphQL hybrid with OpenAPI/Swagger docs auto-generated.

Database: PostgreSQL as primary, with option for MongoDB (unstructured data).

Always normalize DB schemas; migrations managed with Prisma/Migrate or Alembic.

Enforce input validation & sanitization with JSON schema or Pydantic.

Integrate AI/ML services (e.g., data cleaning, mining) as separate microservices.

3. Frontend Engineering Rules

Use Next.js + React + Tailwind for the UI layer.

Maintain design system with reusable components (shadcn/ui, Storybook).

Follow responsive-first, accessibility-first design.

Implement state management with Redux Toolkit or Zustand.

Include real-time feedback (progress bars, loaders, AI suggestions).

4. AI/ML Engineering Rules

Data preprocessing, cleaning, and mining are separate AI pipelines.

Use Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, or PyTorch for model training & inference.

Apply explainable AI (XAI) (e.g., SHAP, LIME) for ML-based suggestions.

Ensure pipeline modularity: ingestion → cleaning → feature engineering → mining → output.

Every AI feature must have a fallback rule-based system if model confidence < threshold.

5. DevOps Rules

Use Docker + Kubernetes for containerization & orchestration.

Maintain CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions or GitLab CI).

Testing stages: unit → integration → end-to-end → load → security.

Monitor with Prometheus + Grafana, log with ELK stack.

Secrets management with Vault or environment variables (no hardcoding).

6. Collaboration & Versioning

Follow Git branching model: main (stable), dev (integration), feature/*, hotfix/*.

Every commit must be atomic, descriptive, and reviewed.

Use issues + pull requests + code reviews for collaboration.

Maintain technical documentation in Markdown + API auto-docs.

7. Ethical & Compliance Rules

Ensure data privacy & GDPR compliance at all stages.

No scraping of restricted or illegal data sources.

Provide user consent + audit trails for every AI decision.

Regularly run bias, fairness, and robustness checks on ML models.